        <div class="about-text">
          <span class="section-badge">Est. 1995</span>
          <h2>Weaving Dreams Since 1995</h2>
          <p>Geetha Tex was founded in the heart of Salem, Tamil Nadu, with a simple yet profound vision — to bring the timeless beauty of handwoven silk sarees to every Indian household.</p>
          <p>What started as a small weaving unit with just two looms has grown into a trusted name in the textile industry. Our founder, inspired by the rich weaving traditions of Tamil Nadu and Kerala, set out to create sarees that blend traditional craftsmanship with contemporary designs.</p>
          <p>Today, Geetha Tex is proud to offer an exquisite collection of Soft Silk sarees, authentic Kerala Kasavu sarees, and bridal collections that are cherished by women across India. Each saree is meticulously handwoven by our team of over 50 skilled artisans who have inherited their craft through generations.</p>
          <p>Located in Salem, known as the "Steel City" and a major hub for the textile industry in Tamil Nadu, we source the finest quality silk and cotton from trusted suppliers. Our commitment to quality, authenticity, and customer satisfaction remains the cornerstone of everything we do.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-highlights">
          <div class="highlight-card">
            <div class="highlight-number">30+</div>
            <div class="highlight-text">Years of Excellence</div>
          </div>
          <div class="highlight-card">
            <div class="highlight-number">50+</div>
            <div class="highlight-text">Master Artisans</div>
          </div>
          <div class="highlight-card">
